      <div rend="parallel">
        <p xml:id="NA243-kiḷavi">itu piriviṭai melinta talaimakaḷ colliyatu.</p>
        <p xml:lang="en">This is what SHE said who had become weak in the time of separation.</p>
        </div>
      <div rend="parallel">
        <lg xml:id="NA243">
<l>            tēmpaṭu cilampiṟ ṟeḷḷaṟa ṟaḻīiya</l>
<l>            tuṟuka layala tūmaṇa laṭaikarai</l>
<l>            yalaṅkuciṉai potuḷiya naṟuvaṭi marāattup</l>
<l>            potumputō ṟalkum pūṅka ṇiruṅkuyil</l>
<l>            kavaṟupeyart taṉṉa nillā vāḻkkaiyiṭ </l>
<l>            ṭakaṟa lōmpumi ṉaṟivuṭai yīreṉak</l>
<l>            kaiyaṟat tuṟappōrk kaḻaṟuva pōla</l>
<l>            meyyuṟa viruntu mēvara nuvala</l>
<l>            viṉṉā tākiya kālaip poruḷvayiṟ</l>
<l>            pirita lāṭavaṟ kiyalpeṉi </l>
<l>            ṉaritumaṉ ṟamma vaṟattiṉum poruḷē.</l>
            </lg>
        <lg xml:lang="en">
<l>At [this] time that is unpleasant,</l>
<l rend="indent">since the flower-eyed dark Koels, that are abiding in every grove</l>
<l rend="indent2">of fragrant mango trees full of swaying branches</l>
<l rend="indent3">on the shore where pure sand settles near thick stones</l>
<l rend="indent">enveloped by clear water from the honey-flowing mountain-side,</l>
<l rend="indent">talk desirously of the feast to take place(?)<note place="foot">T.V.G. dissolves the sandhi in a different way and reads <term xml:lang="ta">iruntu</term> here, that is, the Coels talk while being bodily united.</note></l>
<l rend="indent2">as if they were murmuring:</l>
<l>“beware of departing, o you who possess knowledge,</l>
<l>for(?)<note place="foot"><term xml:lang="ta">iṭṭu</term> is a problem here. Does it mean something like "setting on …" or rather "discarding"?</note> a livelihood<note place="foot"><term xml:lang="ta">vāḻkkai</term> can be understood in a double sense here, namely either the "livelihood", i.e. the wealth HE is after, or simply the "life" which he risks in going.</note> as impermanent as the movement of the dice,”</l>
<l rend="indent4">if [you] say</l>
<l rend="indent3">“it [is] natural for men to separate for wealth,”</l>
<l>more difficult [to bear] than drought indeed [is] wealth.</l>
<lg type="alternate" sameAs="11b">
    <l>rarer than virtue indeed [is] wealth.<note place="foot">Here again we can read either <term xml:lang="ta">vaṟam</term> or <term xml:lang="ta">aṟam</term>. I favour version a, since it would be a clever play on the topos of the rainy season which has just brought nature back to life and ended the drought.</note></l>
</lg>
        </lg>
      </div>
    </body>
